# Domain language

Canonical vocabulary for Project Phoenix, extracted verbatim from
[`design/gdd/GDD.md` §14.1](../../design/gdd/GDD.md#141-glossary-of-terms)
and cross-linked to the defining sections.

This list is the **authoritative naming source** for the project.
Any term used in a spec, tech design, ADR, or piece of code must
either appear here or be proposed for addition via `propose-gdd-edit`.
Synonyms, aliased forms, or near-synonyms are drift and will be
flagged by the `verifier` and `game-designer` subagents.

## Core mechanics and systems

- **Ability Rank** — Star level (★ to ★★★★★) of an ability item; scales base values independently of Ability Level. Defined in GDD §4.8.5.
- **Ability Type** — BASIC, CORE, ULTIMATE, or ITEM. Defined in GDD §4.1.2.
- **Active Equipment** — Equipment that grants abilities (Weapons, Shields, Focuses, Trinkets, Consumables). Defined in GDD §6.1.1.
- **Ailment** — Damage-over-time effect (Poison, Bleed, Ignite). Defined in GDD §7.6.
- **Armor** — Flat reduction to physical damage; from equipment only. Defined in GDD §7.7.2.
- **Base Attribute** — Attribute value from level-up allocation only; used for equipment/ability requirements. Defined in GDD §3.4.1, §6.3.4.
- **Base Stats** — Power numbers that scale with Rank (equipment and abilities). Defined in GDD §6.5.2.
- **Battle Phase** — One of six turn steps; canonical identifiers: `INITIATIVE`, `START_OF_TURN`, `ACTION_SELECTION`, `REACTION_SELECTION`, `EXECUTION`, `END_OF_TURN`. Defined in GDD §7.3.
- **Basic Ability** — Ability granted by Active equipment or innate (Punch, Jab, Rest). Defined in GDD §4.4.
- **Blessing** — Temporary positive effect from an ability; removable. Defined in GDD §4.10.1.
- **Bonus Action** — Quick action, cannot be reacted to, resets at turn start. Defined in GDD §4.5.2.
- **Class Trainer** — NPC (one per class) for class-specific ability crafting (Distill, Learn, Hone) and mastery selection. Defined in GDD §8.1, §11.2.
- **Conditional** — Tag identifying an ability that requires a game-state condition to activate. Defined in GDD §4.5.7.
- **Core Ability** — Main collectible ability; has Rarity and Rank; levelable via loadout Skill Points. Defined in GDD §4.8.1.
- **Curse** — Temporary negative non-damage effect from an ability; removable by Immune. Defined in GDD §4.10.2.
- **Defenses** — Armor, Magic Resistance, and Shield collectively. Defined in GDD §7.7.1.
- **Discipline** — Thematic school grouping abilities (Combat, Agility, Sorcery, Divine); used for effect targeting. Defined in GDD §4.2.1.
- **Distill** — Trainer/Tutor service: break down an ability into Essence. Defined in GDD §11.2.3.
- **Empower** — Core ability tagged EMPOWER that augments a Basic ability. Defined in GDD §4.5.5.
- **Essence** — Universal ability crafting currency from Distilling; used for Learning abilities. Defined in GDD §11.1.3.
- **Fixed Properties** — Equipment properties that never scale (slot, tags, two-handed, requirements). Defined in GDD §6.5.1.
- **Focus** — INT-based off-hand equipment (Grimoire, Tome); caster fantasy. Defined in GDD §6.4.2.
- **Force (naming)** — Naming convention for Mage physical damage abilities (e.g., Force Strike). Defined in GDD §6.4.1.
- **Forge** — Blacksmith service: spend Materials to create specific equipment. Defined in GDD §6.7.2.
- **Gambler** — NPC for random equipment pulls (slot-targeted, gold sink). Defined in GDD §8.1, §11.2.1.
- **Hard Reset** — Initiative resets to 0 on turn start (excess lost); ensures turn character always resolves last in execution. Defined in GDD §7.1.1.
- **Heavy (naming)** — Naming convention for 2H weapon abilities (e.g., Heavy Slash, Heavy Bash). Defined in GDD §6.4.1.
- **Initiative** — Resource accumulated proportional to Speed; at ≥100, character takes a turn (CTB model). Hard resets to 0 after turn. Defined in GDD §7.1.
- **Jab** — Innate Basic ability; unarmed off-hand attack. Defined in GDD §4.4.
- **Learn** — Trainer/Tutor service: spend Essence to create a specific ability. Defined in GDD §11.2.3.
- **Loadout** — Complete character build (attributes, equipment, abilities). Defined in GDD §5.1.
- **Hone** — Trainer/Tutor service: feed duplicate ability copies to increase Rank. Defined in GDD §11.2.3.
- **Materials** — Universal equipment crafting currency from Salvaging; used for Forging equipment. Defined in GDD §11.1.2.
- **Mods** — Predefined effects on equipment; never scale with Rank. Defined in GDD §6.5.3.
- **Normal Action** — Main turn action, triggers Reaction Phase. Defined in GDD §4.5.1.
- **Oracle** — NPC for random ability pulls (class-targeted, gold sink). Defined in GDD §8.1, §11.2.2.
- **Passive (buff)** — Permanent positive effect from an ability; can be suppressed, never removed. Defined in GDD §4.10.1.
- **Passive Equipment** — Equipment that provides stats only (Body, Helmet, Boots, Ring, Amulet). Defined in GDD §6.1.2.
- **Power** — Scaling stat (Combat, Agility, Sorcery, Divine); 1:1 from attributes. Defined in GDD §4.2.2.
- **Punch** — Innate Basic ability; unarmed main-hand attack. Defined in GDD §4.4.
- **Rank** — Star level (★ to ★★★★★); scales Base Stats for both equipment and abilities. Defined in GDD §6.6.2.
- **Rarity** — Item tier (Common→Legendary); determines base Rank, mods, and level requirements. Defined in GDD §6.6.1.
- **Reaction** — Ability used by non-turn characters in response to the turn character's Normal Action. Defined in GDD §4.5.3, §7.3.1.
- **Reactor** — Any non-turn character during the Reaction and Execution phases. Defined in GDD §7.3.1.
- **Resolve** — Resource for Ultimates; generated from combat damage. Defined in GDD §3.5.1.
- **Rest** — Innate Basic ability; restores stamina, always available. Defined in GDD §4.4.
- **Salvage** — Blacksmith service: break down equipment into Materials. Defined in GDD §6.7.1.
- **Shield** — Blessing providing temporary HP (FIFO depletion); displayed on HP bar. Defined in GDD §3.5.2, §4.10.3.
- **Skill Points** — Resource spent in loadout to level Core ability slots (1-10). Defined in GDD §3.6.1, §5.2.3.
- **Suppression** — Temporarily disabling a Passive without removing it; sources include cooldown, Corrupted, and depletion. Defined in GDD §4.5.6.
- **Temper** — Blacksmith service: feed duplicate equipment copies to increase Rank. Defined in GDD §6.7.3.
- **Trigger** — Tag identifying an ability with effects that fire automatically when a condition is met. Defined in GDD §4.5.6.
- **Trinket** — Active equipment slot; grants a reusable activatable ability. Defined in GDD §6.1.1.
- **True Damage** — Bypasses all Defenses. Defined in GDD §4.3.
- **Tutor** — NPC for neutral ability crafting (Distill, Learn, Hone). Defined in GDD §8.1, §11.2.
- **Type (Equipment)** — Foundation defining stats, properties, requirements, ability. Defined in GDD §6.3.1.
- **Ultimate Ability** — Class-specific collectible; costs Resolve, cannot be leveled but can be Honed (ranked up). Defined in GDD §4.1.2.
- **Vanilla** — Equipment with no mods; highest base stats for type. Defined in GDD §6.2.5.
- **Weapon Set** — Paired Main Hand + Off Hand equipment; two sets per character. Defined in GDD §6.1.3.
- **Weapon Swap** — Bonus action to switch active Weapon Set; 2-turn cooldown. Defined in GDD §6.1.3.

## Additional canonical concepts (from GDD, not in §14.1)

These terms appear in the GDD with canonical definitions but are not
in the author's glossary. Treat them with the same discipline as
glossary entries.

### Classes, masteries, attributes

- **Warrior / Mage / Rogue / Neutral** — The three base classes plus the neutral ability pool. Defined in GDD §3.1, §4.1.1.
- **Mastery** — Subclass specialization, one of twelve (four per base class). Defined in GDD §3.2.
- **Mastery Passive Tree** — Each subclass's passive tree unlocked by Mastery Points. Defined in GDD §3.3.
- **Strength / Dexterity / Intelligence / Faith** — The four primary attributes. Defined in GDD §3.4.1.
- **Total Attribute** — Base + all modifiers; the effective value used for scaling. Defined in GDD §3.4.1.

### Resources

- **Health (HP)**, **Mana**, **Stamina** — Primary character resources. Defined in GDD §3.5.
- **Initiative** (see glossary above).
- **Bonus Action charges** — Resource gating Bonus Actions; default max 1, resets at turn start. Defined in GDD §3.5.

### Action and ability taxonomy

- **Action Type** — NORMAL / REACTION / BONUS / PASSIVE. Defined in GDD §4.1.3.
- **Tags** — Ability classification set: ATTACK, SPELL, MELEE, RANGED, AOE, BUFF, DEBUFF, PHYSICAL, MAGIC, RECOVERY, CONSUMABLE, EMPOWER, TRIGGER, CONDITIONAL, BLESSING, CURSE. Defined in GDD §4.1.4.
- **Percentage Empower / Flat Empower** — Two mutually exclusive Empower classes with distinct scaling and variance rules. Defined in GDD §4.5.5.
- **Trigger Response Types** — Self-contained effect vs ability proxy. Defined in GDD §4.5.6.
- **Variance Tiers** — Consistent / Standard / Volatile design guideline for ability damage range width. Defined in GDD §4.6.1.

### Status effects

- **Stealth** / **Invulnerable** / **Immune** — Specific Blessings. Defined in GDD §4.10.3.
- **Slowed** / **Dazed** / **Corrupted** — Specific Curses. Defined in GDD §4.10.3.
- **Poison** / **Bleed** / **Ignite** — The three Ailments. Defined in GDD §4.10.3, §7.6.

### Combat math

- **Aggregate modifier** — Feeds always-on character totals (max resources, crit chance, etc.). Defined in GDD §4.6.5.
- **Resolution modifier** — Applies when a specific damage or healing instance is calculated. Defined in GDD §4.6.5.
- **Pre-mitigation damage** — Ability roll + flats + additive resolution % + crit; input to the mitigation pipeline. Defined in GDD §4.6.5, §7.7.4.
- **Ignite Priority Queue** — Non-stacking Ignite resolution rule. Defined in GDD §7.6.3.

### Equipment

- **Equipment Slots** — Main Hand, Off Hand, Trinket, Consumable 1, Consumable 2, Amulet, Ring, Helmet, Body, Boots (10 total). Defined in GDD §6.1.
- **Active set** vs **Inactive set** — The two Weapon Sets. Defined in GDD §6.1.3.
- **Variance (Body / Helmet / Boots)** — Per-attribute stat themes; see GDD §6.4.3.

### Structure and progression

- **Hub (Town)** — Central navigation structure. Defined in GDD §8.1.
- **Campaign** / **Zone** / **Boss Encounter** — PvE progression structure. Defined in GDD §8.2.
- **Casual PvP** / **Ranked PvP** / **Tournaments** — PvP modes. Defined in GDD §8.4.
- **Gold** — Primary currency. Defined in GDD §11.1.1.

## Forbidden aliases (catch drift early)

When writing code, specs, or docs, **do not use** the following
aliases — they name concepts that already have canonical names above:

- "stat" → use the specific stat's canonical name (Speed, Accuracy, etc.) or "Base Stats" when referring to the scaled-by-rank family.
- "buff" as a general noun when you mean a Blessing or Passive — those are the canonical types.
- "debuff" as a general noun when you mean a Curse or Ailment — those are the canonical types.
- "spell" as distinct from "ability" — all spells are abilities; use "ability with SPELL tag" when needed.
- "crafting currency" — use Materials (equipment) or Essence (abilities) specifically.
- "turn step" or "phase number" — use the `BattlePhase` identifiers: `INITIATIVE`, `START_OF_TURN`, `ACTION_SELECTION`, `REACTION_SELECTION`, `EXECUTION`, `END_OF_TURN`.
- "random pull" without a specific NPC — use "Gambler pull" (equipment) or "Oracle pull" (abilities).

When unsure whether a term is canonical, default to the exact
phrasing used in the GDD. If it is not in the GDD, propose adding
it here (via `propose-gdd-edit` if it is a new design concept, or
via a scope ADR if it is a derivation).
